INSERT INTO `attorney_terms_and_conditions` (`id`, `terms_and_conditions`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1, '<strong>ATTORNEYS’ RESPONSIBILITIES WITH CLIENTS:</strong> YourBestLawyer.com LLC operates as a marketplace, not a law firm. We provide consumers with general information, allowing them to select categories based on the attorney expertise they seek. Clients then submit a bid. If a bid is directed to the category in which your profile is featured, you will have the opportunity to review incoming leads and decide whether you are interested in pursuing them or you can choose to reject them.<br><br>\r\n\r\nIf a client selects you as their attorney, and if you accept their contract, you will be entering into a contractual agreement. In doing so, you are obligated to uphold the highest standards of ethical conduct and fulfill fiduciary duties and duties of care throughout the duration of the client engagement.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<strong>DURATION OF ATTORNEY ABLE TO USE YOURBESTLAWYER.COM PLATFORM AND HAVE ACCESS TO LEADS:</strong> As long as Attorney is current with the monthly subscription of $165.00 per month, they can use the platform and have access to all leads. If attorney violates any form of professional conduct or is reckless in the duty of care to the client, YourBestLawyer.com LLC has the right to decline services to the attorney.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<strong>TERMINATION OF REPRESENTATION AND POST-REPRESENTATION MATTERS WITH CLIENTS OBTAINED FROM YOURBESTLAWYER.COM LLC:</strong> Either party may terminate the representation at any time, subject to attorneys’ obligations under the Rules of Professional Conduct and the approval of the court if the matter is in litigation. Unless previously terminated, Attorney representation will terminate upon completion of the legal services.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<strong>ATTORNEYS AGREE TO USE YOURBESTLAWYER.COM LLC PROVIDED AGREEMENTS:</strong> The attorney agrees to utilize contracts provided by YourBestLawyer.com LLC. Copies of our online contracts are enclosed in Attachment 2. The attorney commits not to modify any language within our contracts. If additional documents require the client\'s signature, the attorney must have the client sign them directly. However, no alterations to any language in the original contract are permitted. To view all our client attorney agreements, click HERE.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<strong>REFUND:</strong> IF YOU OR THE CLIENT TERMINATE REPRESENTATION BEFORE LEGAL WORK HAS BEEN COMPLETED, YOU WILL HAVE TO PROCESS A CANCELLATION AND REFUND THROUGH YOUR OFFICE. The flat fee paid through YourBestLawyer.com LLC will not be refunded since that was the cost you, the attorney, paid out of pocket to obtain the client.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<strong>NO ADVICE REGARDING THIS FEE AGREEMENT:</strong> No one is acting as your counsel with respect to this agreement. If you wish to be advised on whether you should enter into this agreement, it is recommended you consult with independent counsel of your choice.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<strong>COUNTERPARTS:</strong> This agreement may be signed by the parties in different counterparts and the signature pages combined will create a document binding on all parties.\r\n', 'Enabled', '2024-09-23 16:04:20', '2024-09-23 16:04:20');
