ement. The client may consult independent counsel before entering into the agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>NO GUARANTEES:</strong> The client understands that no guarantees, predictions, or promises regarding the outcome of the case can be made.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>COUNTERPARTS:</strong> This agreement may be signed in different counterparts, and the combined signature pages will create a binding document.</p>\r\n', 'Enable', '2024-09-24 18:50:13', '2024-09-24 18:50:13'),
(9, 3, 'Top Notch', '<strong>CONTINGENCY FEE:</strong> If a personal injury case goes to litigation, the contingency fee will not exceed 40%.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ATTORNEY’S FEES IF DISCHARGED BEFORE COMPLETION OF THE CASE:</strong> If attorney services are terminated before the case is finalized, the attorney will be entitled to quantum meruit fees. These are fair compensation fees based on the work performed and prevailing market rates. The attorney will not bill more than $400.00 per hour for this category.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SCOPE OF SERVICES:</strong> The client employs the attorney to represent the client’s claim in obtaining a final judgment or settlement. The client authorizes the attorney to act on their behalf in all matters related to the claim and to negotiate on behalf of the client. The firm will not settle the case without the client’s consent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Client agrees to cooperate fully with the attorney, be truthful, keep the attorney advised of developments, and update any changes in address or telephone numbers. The client must also cooperate with health care providers, follow prescribed medical treatments, and abide by this contract.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the claim involves a motor vehicle accident and the responsible parties have no liability insurance or insufficient coverage, the attorney is authorized to submit uninsured or underinsured motorist claims to the client\'s insurance company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>LIMITED REPRESENTATION:</strong> The client understands that representation is limited to the matters set forth above. Any additional legal representation will require a separate agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>LEGAL FEES ARE CONTINGENT:</strong> If no recovery is obtained, no payment will be due to the attorney.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ADDITIONAL DOCUMENTS REQUIRED:</strong> The client agrees to sign any additional documents necessary for the representation, such as powers of attorney, medical authorization forms, and Medicare release forms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>COSTS:</strong> The attorney may advance costs for the client in accordance with ethics rules. The client is responsible for repaying costs, which may include charges for medical records, expert witnesses, travel, depositions, and other litigation-related expenses. Costs will be deducted from any recovery after attorney\'s fees are calculated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PRIOR ATTORNEY LIENS:</strong> The client consents for the attorney to honor any prior attorney liens for costs and services from the client’s share of the recovery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>CREDITOR’S LIENS:</strong> With the client’s and creditor’s consent, the attorney may honor creditor liens (including healthcare providers) from the client’s recovery. The client’s unpaid medical expenses remain the client’s responsibility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>DISCHARGE OR WITHDRAWAL:</strong> The client may discharge the law firm at any time. The law firm may withdraw with the client’s consent or for good cause, such as breach of the agreement or refusal to cooperate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>AUTHORIZATION TO PROVIDE INFORMATION TO THIRD PARTIES:</strong> The client authorizes the attorney to provide relevant information (e.g., contact or insurance information) to healthcare providers and to obtain medical records to proceed with the case. The attorney may also disclose necessary medical records to obtain recovery for the client.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>DOCUMENT RETENTION:</strong> At the end of the representation, the attorney will turn over the file to the client. If the client does not want the file, they agree it may be destroyed per the attorney’s document retention policy, which currently allows file destruction five years after the end of representation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ARBITRATION OF FEE DISPUTES:</strong> Any fee disputes will be resolved through the State Bar’s Fee Arbitration Program.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>NO ADVICE REGARDING THIS FEE AGREEMENT:</strong> No legal counsel is provided regarding this agreement. The client may consult independent counsel before entering into the agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>NO GUARANTEES:</strong> The client understands that no guarantees, predictions, or promises regarding the outcome of the case can be made.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>COUNTERPARTS:</strong> This agreement may be signed in different counterparts, and the combined signature pages will create a binding document.</p>\r\n', 'Enable', '2024-09-24 18:50:13', '2024-09-24 18:50:13');
