(10, 5, 'Novice', '<strong>YOURBESTLAWYER.COM FEE:</strong> The attorney has already paid for this portion.<br><br>\n\n<p><strong>WHAT IS COVERED:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li><strong>a. Means Test:</strong> Analysis of the client’s financial situation and assistance in determining whether to file a bankruptcy petition.</li>\n    <li><strong>b. Preparation and Filing:</strong> Preparation and filing of the petition, statement of financial affairs, and necessary documents for the case.</li>\n    <li><strong>c. Representation at the 341(a) Meeting:</strong> Representation of the client at the Meeting of Creditors.</li>\n    <li><strong>d. Telephone Conferences:</strong> Telephone conferences with the client, trustee, creditors, or related parties.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Representation is limited to the services specified above.</p>\n\n<p>The client acknowledges that a filing fee of $335.00 is separate from legal fees and must be paid before filing the case.</p>\n\n<p>The client understands that a thorough credit report must be conducted to ensure all creditors are included. This report incurs a separate fee, with a maximum of $45.00 for individual filers and $90.00 for joint filers.</p>\n\n<p>Additionally, the client understands that there are two required courses mandated by the United States Bankruptcy Court that are NOT included in the legal fees and must be covered by the client to obtain a discharge.</p>\n\n<p><strong>IMPORTANT NOTICE:</strong> Bankruptcy will not be filed until all fees are paid in full.</p>\n\n<p>If the client decides to terminate services before completion of representation, a minimum non-refundable flat fee of $250.00 will cover administrative costs, plus a minimum of $25.00 per month while the file remains open.</p>\n\n<p><strong>COSTS:</strong> The client acknowledges that if their disposable income exceeds after the attorney\'s analysis, they might need to file a Chapter 13 bankruptcy or attempt debt negotiation instead of the initially contracted Chapter 7 bankruptcy. The client agrees that additional work by the attorney may result in additional legal fees. The attorney will not change the bankruptcy type or negotiate without the client\'s consent and a new written fee agreement. The client agrees to pay all actual out-of-pocket costs incurred by the attorney, including filing fees, expert witness fees, travel expenses, and other associated costs. Legal fees do not cover adversary filings, motion for relief fees, expert witnesses, transcripts, or other miscellaneous motions.</p>\n\n<p>The attorney may cover certain out-of-pocket costs on behalf of the client but reserves the right to seek reimbursement.</p>\n\n<p><strong>DISCHARGE OR WITHDRAWAL:</strong> The client may discharge the attorney at any time. The attorney may withdraw with the client’s consent or for good cause, including the client’s breach of the agreement or failure to cooperate.</p>\n\n<p><strong>TERMINATION OF REPRESENTATION:</strong> If the client terminates representation before completion, they must process cancellation and refunds through the attorney. Representation will terminate upon completion of the described legal services. The attorney has no ongoing obligation to represent the client unless retained for additional services.</p>\n\n<p><strong>REFUND:</strong> If the client terminates representation before services are completed, they must process cancellation and refunds through the attorney. The attorney is entitled to prepare a detailed itemization, billing at a minimum hourly rate of $175.00 for the attorney and $75.00 for assistance.</p>\n\n<p><strong>CLIENT’S RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong> The attorney cannot effectively represent the client without cooperation and assistance. The client agrees to provide promptly all relevant information and documents, assist in discovery and trial preparation, respond timely to communications, and inform the attorney of any changes in contact information.</p>\n\n<p><strong>SETTLEMENT:</strong> The attorney will not enter into a settlement without the client’s consent.</p>\n\n<p><strong>DOCUMENT RETENTION:</strong> At the end of representation, the attorney will turn over the file to the client. If the client does not want the file, they agree it may be destroyed per the attorney’s document retention policy, currently allowing destruction five years after termination.</p>\n\n<p><strong>THIRD PARTY:</strong> If legal fees are paid by a third party, both the client and the third party understand that the attorney’s ethical duties of confidentiality and communication are owed to the client. All decisions regarding the case shall be discussed only with the client unless express written permission is given. Refunds will be returned to the party who provided the funds.</p>\n\n<p><strong>COMMUNICATIONS:</strong> The attorney will attempt to return phone calls within 24 hours and encourages email communications. Non-lawyer staff may communicate with the client as appropriate. Confidential information will not be disclosed to third parties without the client\'s express direction, and the client will receive copies of all relevant documents and correspondence.</p>\n\n<p><strong>NO ADVICE REGARDING THIS FEE AGREEMENT:</strong> No one is acting as the client\'s counsel regarding this agreement. The client is advised to consult independent counsel if needed.</p>\n\n<p><strong>OTHER DOCUMENTS:</strong> The client may need to sign additional documents, including FULL DISCLOSURE & ACCURACY (11 U.S.C. § 527 (a)(2)) and FRAUD & CONCEALMENT PROHIBITED (11 U.S.C. § 342 (b)(2)(A) and (B)). These documents emphasize the importance of accurate disclosures in bankruptcy filings. Failure to comply may lead to case dismissal and legal consequences.</p>\n\n<p><strong>NO EXPRESSED GUARANTEE:</strong> The client understands that no one in the legal field can guarantee, predict, or promise any outcome regarding their case.</p>\n\n<p><strong>COUNTERPARTS:</strong> This agreement may be signed in different counterparts, and combined signature pages will create a binding document.</p>\n', 'Enable', '2024-09-24 18:55:21', '2024-09-24 18:55:21'),
(11, 5, 'Experienced', '<strong>YOURBESTLAWYER.COM FEE:</strong> \n<p>Attorney has already paid for this portion.</p>\n\n<strong>WHAT IS COVERED:</strong> \n<ul>\n    <li>a. Means test. - Analysis of the Client’s financial situation and advice and assistance to Client in determining whether to file a petition for Bankruptcy.</li>\n    <li>b. Preparation and filing of the petition, statement of financial affairs, and documents required for the filing of the case for the Client.</li>\n    <li>c. Representation of the Client at the 341 (a) Meeting of Creditors.</li>\n    <li>d. Telephone conferences with you, your Trustee, your Trustee’s counsel, your creditors or any parties related to your case.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Representation of the Client is limited to the services specified above.</p>\n\n<p>Client understands that there is a filing fee of $335.00 separate to the legal fees and it must be paid before filing the case.</p>\n\n<p>The client acknowledges that the attorney must conduct a thorough credit report to ensure the inclusion of all creditors. This credit report incurs a separate fee, with a maximum cost of $45.00 for individual filers and no more than $90.00 for joint filing.</p>\n\n<p>Client understands that there are two courses required by the United States Bankruptcy Court that are NOT included in the legal fees. These courses must be covered by the client in order to get discharge.</p>\n\n<strong>BANKRUPTCY WILL NOT BE FILED UNTIL ALL FEES ARE PAID IN FULL.</strong>\n\n<p>If client decides to terminate services prior to the completion of representation, notwithstanding any attorneys’ fees actually incurred, to cover administrative costs (opening case, opening physical file, computer database, entry and accounting system) the client agrees that in all cases, a minimum non-refundable flat fee of $250.00 of the legal fees paid to the Attorney to cover this administrative cost, additionally a minimum of $25.00 per month that the file is open.</p>\n\n<strong>COSTS:</strong> \n<p>You acknowledge and understand that if they exceed disposable income after the Attorney analysis of their financial situation, client might be required to file a Chapter 13 bankruptcy or attempt a debt negotiation, instead of the Chapter 7 bankruptcy originally contracted for.</p>\n<p>If this occurs, client acknowledges and agrees that they were advised that there could be additional work by the Attorney, and thus additional legal fees. The Attorney will not change the client to a different type of bankruptcy or debt negotiation without the Client\'s consent and a new written fee agreement. You agree to pay for all actual out-of-pocket costs Attorney incurs on your behalf. Typical costs include: filing fees, service of process, depositions, expert witness fees, travel expenses, long-distance telephone calls, Federal Express, courier services, and delivery charges, online database retrieval charges (Lexis, Westlaw, etc.), transcripts, private investigation costs, and other miscellaneous costs reasonably associated with the representation of the Client\'s case. Also, legal fees do not cover the following: adversary filing, Motion for Relief fees, expert witnesses, transcripts, and other miscellaneous motions.</p>\n\n<p>Attorney may elect to cover certain out-of-pocket costs on behalf of you, but Attorney reserves the right to seek reimbursement from you. You agree to reimburse us for such out-of-pocket costs.</p>\n\n<strong>DISCHARGE OR WITHDRAWAL:</strong> \n<p>Client may discharge Attorney at any time. Attorney may withdraw with Client\'s consent or for good cause. Good cause includes Client\'s breach of this Agreement, Client\'s refusal to cooperate with Attorney or to follow Attorney’s advice on a material matter or any other fact or circumstance that would render Attorney\'s continuing representation unjust or unethical.</p>\n\n<strong>TERMINATION OF REPRESENTATION AND POST-REPRESENTATION MATTERS:</strong> \n<p>THIS PARAGRAPH DOES NOT INVOLVE YOURBESTLAWYER.COM. IF YOU TERMINATE REPRESENTATION BEFORE ATTORNEY HAS COMPLETED SERVICES, YOU WILL HAVE TO PROCESS A CANCELLATION AND REFUND THROUGH THE ATTORNEY. Either party may terminate the representation at any time, subject to attorneys’ obligations under the Rules of Professional Conduct and the approval of the court if the matter is in litigation. Unless previously terminated, Attorney representation will terminate upon completion of the legal services described in this agreement. You understand Attorney has no continuing obligation to represent you unless you retain Attorney to provide additional advice or services.</p>\n\n<strong>REFUND:</strong> \n<p>THIS PARAGRAPH DOES NOT INVOLVE YOURBESTLAWYER.COM. IF YOU TERMINATE REPRESENTATION BEFORE ATTORNEY HAS COMPLETED SERVICES, YOU WILL HAVE TO PROCESS A CANCELLATION AND REFUND THROUGH THE ATTORNEY. The attorney is entitled to prepare a detailed itemization with a minimum hourly rate for the attorney at no less than $250.00 per hour and bill for assistants at $125.00 per hour.</p>\n\n<strong>CLIENT’S RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong> \n<p>Attorney cannot effectively represent you without your cooperation and assistance. You agree to cooperate fully with us and to provide promptly all information known or available to you that is relevant to Attorney’s representation. Your obligations include timely providing requested information and documents, assisting in discovery, disclosure and trial preparation, cooperating in scheduling and related matters, responding timely to telephone calls and correspondence, and informing us of changes in your address and telephone numbers.</p>\n\n<strong>SETTLEMENT:</strong> \n<p>Attorney will not enter into a settlement without your consent.</p>\n\n<strong>DOCUMENT RETENTION:</strong> \n<p>At the end of the representation, Attorney will turn over the file to you. If you do not want the file, you agree the file may be destroyed in accordance with the attorney\'s document retention policy. Currently, it is attorney\'s policy to destroy files five years after the termination of the representation.</p>\n\n<strong>THIRD PARTY:</strong> \n<p>Your legal fees are being paid by a third party. Both you and the third party must understand that attorney’s ethical duties of confidentiality and communications are owed to you, not to the person paying the fees. All decisions regarding the legal status and strategy of your case shall be discussed only with you unless you give express written permission. Any refund shall be returned to the party who provided the funds.</p>\n\n<strong>COMMUNICATIONS:</strong> \n<p>Attorney will make every attempt to return all phone calls within 24 hours. Attorney encourages email communications as well. Non-lawyer staff may be directed to communicate with you, if appropriate. Attorney will not communicate confidential information about the representation to third persons, including your family members, unless you specifically direct us to do so. Attorney will send you copies of all relevant documents and correspondence that Attorney receives in the case so that you can maintain a complete file of the legal matter. All communication with you will be billed for in accordance with the terms of the fee agreement.</p>\n\n<strong>NO ADVICE REGARDING THIS FEE AGREEMENT:</strong> \n<p>No one is not acting as your counsel with respect to this agreement. If you wish to be advised on whether you should enter into this agreement, it is recommended you consult with independent counsel of your choice.</p>\n\n<strong>OTHER DOCUMENTS ATTORNEY MAY NEED YOU TO SIGN:</strong> \n<p>You may be asked to sign additional documents, like FULL DISCLOSURE & ACCURACY (11 U.S.C. § 527 (a) (2)) and FRAUD & CONCEALMENT PROHIBITED (11 U.S.C. § 342 (B) (2) (A) and (B)). Essentially, these documents emphasize the importance of adhering to bankruptcy rules. According to 11 U.S.C. § 342 (b) (2) (A) and (B), when filing for bankruptcy, you must recognize that the information you provide is submitted to the court under penalty of perjury and hiding assets or making false statements can lead to fines or imprisonment. The U.S. Attorney General may also review the information. Under 11 U.S.C. § 527 (a) (2), it\'s crucial to be accurate and complete in disclosing details to your attorney, trustee, and the court, covering assets, liabilities, and a precise monthly budget. Non-compliance may result in case dismissal and potential legal consequences. Acknowledging this confirms your understanding of these requirements.</p>\n\n<strong>NO EXPRESSED GUARANTEE, PREDICTION OF RESULT OR ACCOMPLISHMENT:</strong> \n<p>Client understands that NO ONE employed in the legal field can make any guarantees, promises, predictions, expectations or statements regarding the disposition, result or outcome of the above matter.</p>\n\n<strong>COUNTERPARTS:</strong> \n<p>This agreement may be signed by the parties in different counterparts and the signature pages combined will create a document binding on all parties.</p>\n', 'Enable', '2024-09-24 18:55:21', '2024-09-24 18:55:21'),
